Sevendust is the self-titled debut album by American alternative metal band Sevendust.
 The Japan reissue has live versions of "Bitch" and "Prayer" as ending bonus tracks.
 Sevendust appeared on the Billboard 200, remained there for sixteen weeks and peaked at 165 on April 4, 1998.
 The album went gold on May 19, 1999, and had by January 2011 sold 732,000 copies in the U.S.
 The album was re-mastered and re-released on June 21, 2010 entitled "The Definitive Edition", featuring two b-sides and two live tracks.

"My Ruin" appeared on the Mortal Kombat: More Kombat album, credited under the band's original name, "Crawlspace". "Too Close to Hate" appeared on the Masterminds album.
 The song "Terminator" was featured in MTV television series Celebrity Deathmatch.
